snippet: As much as the young in Cuba welcome political opening and economic reform, such changes are unlikely to filter down to their lives anytime soon.
abstract: Many Cuban youth are cynical about the pace and degree of change heralded by normalization of relations with United States, which is symbolized by reopening of US embassy in Havana; promise of prosperity seems very far off to young, and their skepticism about change points to challenge government faces in managing its population's expectations.
lead_paragraph: As much as the young in Cuba welcome political opening and economic reform, such changes are unlikely to filter down to their lives anytime soon.

headline.main: Cuban Youth See New U.S. Embassy, but Same Old Drab Life
headline.print_headline: Optimism in Cuba, Except Among the Young
